      | 10. Is there a clear curriculum for each belt, and is it posted for students to see?
    div.hidden.mt-2.text-left.p-4.bg-gray-100.rounded-md.shadow-inner(id='faq-10')
      p Just as important as lineage is transparency. Students should always know whatâ€™s expected of them. A well-run school will have a clearly defined curriculum for each belt level â€” posted on the wall, provided in handouts, or made available online.
      p In my studio, every student received a curriculum sheet tailored to the belt they were working toward. The complete system was posted on large wall charts above the mirror, and every assistant instructor had a curriculum workbook to ensure consistency.
