      | 11. How do students progress through the ranks and earn their next belt?
    div.hidden.mt-2.text-left.p-4.bg-gray-100.rounded-md.shadow-inner(id='faq-11')
      p Some schools guarantee belt promotions after a set number of classes â€” but quality schools take a different approach. Advancement should be based on mastery, not attendance.
      p In my system, students begin as white belts and progress through yellow, orange, purple, blue, green, brown, red, red/black, and finally black belt. Advancement requires the student to fully understand and demonstrate the material for their current rank â€” and meet the same high standard as every other student at that level.
