      p I also believe strongly in safety and control. Martial arts is physical, and bumps and bruises are part of training â€” but excessive injuries, broken bones, or head trauma shouldn't be common in any well-run school. Instructors and advanced students should always demonstrate restraint and control, especially when working with newer students.
