      p Over time, we expand into areas like throws, joint locks, grappling, weapon defense, freestyle sparring, and street-oriented scenarios â€” all layered in at appropriate stages of a student's development.
      p For advanced students, I also incorporated firearms training into the curriculum â€” with a focus on tactical firearm use for self-defense situations. This training wasnâ€™t about glorifying violence, but about equipping students with the knowledge and discipline to handle real-world threats proficiently and responsibly when unarmed defense might not be enough.
